00:53:07,740 --> 00:53:21,424
A couple questions. Thanks for doing the talk by the way. First question, as far as playtesting and stuff, did you guys mostly just rely on yourselves and family and things like that? Or did you try to do outside sort of playtest scenarios?

900
00:53:22,144 --> 00:53:36,309
A lot of the early stuff was internal and then it would be family members. We actually did like a, we did a broader test through Steam. We put the game, we had like a Steam ID and we made it the beta available to a lot of people who we knew.

901
00:53:36,999 --> 00:53:38,900
and then we put metrics into the game

902
00:53:39,420 --> 00:53:42,821
like we asked we had you know uh... surveys to give us information but then

903
00:53:42,861 --> 00:53:45,582
we had metrics in the game like where were they dying and what were they using

904
00:53:45,602 --> 00:53:47,563
the moves properly and where were they using them

905
00:53:48,143 --> 00:53:49,884
and we would have them send that stuff back to us

906
00:53:50,684 --> 00:53:52,865
uh... so we did kind of a broad one like that and then

907
00:53:53,745 --> 00:53:55,806
And then we did a lot near the end.

908
00:53:55,826 --> 00:53:58,267
You know, every few days we would have people come in

909
00:53:58,287 --> 00:54:03,688
and play in a room and we would stream the video to everyone,

910
00:54:03,908 --> 00:54:06,129
but in particular the designers could watch them play through

