00:54:21,256 --> 00:54:24,139
Okay, and just one other quick thing off the top of my head,

919
00:54:24,499 --> 00:54:28,403
difficulty as far as adding the two player component.

920
00:54:29,584 --> 00:54:32,847
How did you worry about adjusting difficulty?

921
00:54:32,907 --> 00:54:34,749
Or was it more of a thought, well,

922
00:54:35,069 --> 00:54:37,452
if playing two players it becomes just easier?

923
00:54:37,752 --> 00:54:40,615
Or do you consciously try to make it more difficult

924
00:54:40,655 --> 00:54:41,295
to balance it out?

925
00:54:41,736 --> 00:54:43,357
Yeah, so yeah, the question is.

926
00:54:45,354 --> 00:54:48,238
adding two players, how did we handle that?

927
00:54:48,278 --> 00:54:49,259
Were we concerned about that?

928
00:54:50,201 --> 00:54:51,723
Yeah, we were extremely concerned about that.

929
00:54:52,143 --> 00:54:53,265
There was a person on the team

930
00:54:53,305 --> 00:54:54,607
who was pushing for two players,

931
00:54:55,328 --> 00:54:57,211
and we were doubtful because there was

932
00:54:57,231 --> 00:54:58,452
a lot of costs associated,

933
00:54:58,593 --> 00:55:01,036
and he finally kind of won us over.

934
00:55:03,058 --> 00:55:07,020
At a certain level, we kind of eventually accepted that the two-player game is going

935
00:55:07,040 --> 00:55:12,243
to basically be easier, but also harder because of the dimension swapping with the platforming,

936
00:55:12,283 --> 00:55:16,866
which was kind of brutal to players, which is why we added this bubbling mechanic where

937
00:55:16,906 --> 00:55:17,847
the second player can bubble.

938
00:55:18,707 --> 00:55:23,190
We just kind of accepted that it was going to be easier, that it wasn't probably going

939
00:55:23,210 --> 00:55:24,871
to get a lot of use from people.

940
00:55:27,636 --> 00:55:32,260
and I mean there are adjustments that might not be obvious when you play, like basically the enemies become stronger.

941
00:55:32,800 --> 00:55:35,482
But very simple adjustments. Basically our attitude was

942
00:55:36,843 --> 00:55:41,507
we played it, we had people play it, and we wanted to make sure that it flowed pretty well, but it wasn't our primary focus.

943
00:55:41,547 --> 00:55:43,829
We just wanted to make sure that it was reasonably good.

944
00:55:44,689 --> 00:55:45,590
That makes sense. Thank you.

945
00:55:45,610 --> 00:55:47,211
Hi.

946
00:55:47,922 --> 00:55:53,504
During your presentation, you were talking about how you always said yes to adding new personality in your game.

947
00:55:54,284 --> 00:55:59,106
Did you ever feel that there were times where ideas were presented that didn't really fit your game,

948
00:55:59,146 --> 00:56:02,247
and how did you decide that those should not be a part of the guacamelee?

