00:56:03,007 --> 00:56:08,709
Yeah, so to repeat the question, we added a lot of personality, and I said that we said yes to lots of stuff,

950
00:56:08,929 --> 00:56:12,030
but how do you mediate stuff that doesn't fit with the vision?

951
00:56:13,958 --> 00:56:15,759
Yeah, I'm not sure quite how to answer that.

952
00:56:16,020 --> 00:56:17,721
I mean, the basic answer is,

953
00:56:18,201 --> 00:56:19,342
yes, we had problems with that,

954
00:56:19,843 --> 00:56:22,104
and the producer basically made the call.

955
00:56:22,645 --> 00:56:25,187
That was kind of the essence of it.

956
00:56:25,267 --> 00:56:27,509
I mean, that wasn't always true,

957
00:56:27,589 --> 00:56:28,790
because, you know, sometimes, like,

958
00:56:29,110 --> 00:56:30,571
say the producer wants to push something out,

959
00:56:30,631 --> 00:56:32,112
but then the team kind of revolts on it,

960
00:56:32,393 --> 00:56:34,154
and says, no, this must stay.

961
00:56:34,694 --> 00:56:35,715
And so the producer was...

962
00:56:36,876 --> 00:56:41,418
I kind of view the producer, it's like, kind of like the prime minister in a prime ministerial system.

963
00:56:41,458 --> 00:56:47,121
It's like the prime minister is the leader, and he's kind of in charge, and he gets to say what goes,

964
00:56:47,521 --> 00:56:50,382
but he's still subject to the other ministers.

965
00:56:50,422 --> 00:56:52,543
The other ministers can boot him out of the cabinet, right?

966
00:56:52,583 --> 00:56:54,884
They can kick him out if they really don't like what he's doing,

967
00:56:54,964 --> 00:56:56,565
and that's kind of the attitude we took with it.

968
00:56:56,605 --> 00:56:59,386
Like, the producer is in charge, and he's going to make the hard calls,

969
00:56:59,986 --> 00:57:04,808
but the people on the floor can still kind of revolt over it as a collective if they need to, if they feel they need to.

970
00:57:04,828 --> 00:57:06,009
All right, thank you.

